    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSince https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/cba07dad494558a4a06e25a35521041864697be3:\n\n```sh\necho foo > repro.txt; nvim -u NONE --cmd 'au TextChanged * sil! update' repro.txt\n```\nType `vd`, it's normal mode now, but `-- VISUAL --` still shown in the bottom.\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n As above.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo message shown when in normal mode.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nSince https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/cba07dad494558a4a06e25a35521041864697be3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from source",
